 <title>SAP Product Installation</title>

 <para>
  This section will guide you through the installation of SAP media kits you
  received from SAP.
 </para>

 <sect2 xml:id="sec.s4s.install.sap.welcome">
  <title>First Steps</title>

  <para>
   These first steps are only relevant during the installation workflow.
  </para>

  <remark>
   Add screenshots below. - sknorr, 2016-01-14
  </remark>

  <procedure>
   <step>
    <para>
     When the system has booted, you will be presented with the screen
     <guimenu>Welcome</guimenu>.
     Proceed with <guimenu>Next</guimenu>.
    </para>
   </step>
   <step>
    <para>
     The screen <guimenu>Network Settings</guimenu> will now open.
     This gives you another chance to change the network settings.
    </para>
    <para>
     When you are finished configuring networking, proceed with
     <guimenu>Next</guimenu>.
    </para>
    <important>
     <title>Configure Networking as Recommended by SAP</title>
     <para>
      Make sure to configure the network connection as recommended by the
      documentation of your SAP application.
     </para>
    </important>
    <para>
     For details regarding network configuration, see
     <citetitle>
      &admin;, Chapter 19 <quote>Basic Networking</quote>,
      Section 19.4 <quote>Configuring a Network Connection with YaST</quote>
     </citetitle> (&docaddress;).
    </para>
    <note>
     <title>
      The Screen <guimenu>Welcome</guimenu> May Appear Shortly
     </title>
     <para>
      Before the next screen appears, the <guimenu>Welcome</guimenu> screen may
      appear again for a few seconds before the following page loads.
     </para>
     <remark>
      This note necessary? (It does appear for around 8s for me.)
      - sknorr, 2016-01-14
     </remark>
    </note>
   </step>
   <step>
    <para>
     You can now choose how to continue:
    </para>
    <variablelist>
     <varlistentry>
      <term>
       <guimenu>Create SAP file systems and start SAP product
       installation</guimenu>
      </term>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Allows installing an SAP product or setting up the system as a
        server providing SAP installation routines to other systems.
       </para>
       <remark>Correct terminology? - sknorr, 2016-01-14</remark>
       <para>
        Continue with <xref linkend="sec.s4s.install.sap.product"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>
     <varlistentry>
      <term>
       <guimenu>Only create SAP HANA file systems, do not install SAP products
       now</guimenu>
      </term>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Only create an SAP HANA file system.
       </para>
       <remark>
        For whatever reason there is no way out after clicking Next. You click
        OK twice and suddenly, there is a/no HANA fs. - sknorr, 2016-01-14
       </remark>
       <important>
        <title>Use Hardware Certified for SAP HANA</title>
        <para>
         To use this functionality, your hardware needs to be certified
         for SAP HANA.
         Otherwise, this option will not create a new file system and the
         installation workflow ends at this point.
        </para>
        <remark>
         Unfortunately, the installer claims to have the "SAP file system
         creation successfully done" at this point. Meh. - sknorr, 2016-01-14
        </remark>
       </important>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>
     <varlistentry>
      <term>
       <guimenu>Finish wizard and proceed to OS login</guimenu>
      </term>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Do not install an SAP application and continue to the login screen of
        &sles4sap;.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
    <para>
     Proceed with <guimenu>Next</guimenu>.
    </para>
   </step>
  </procedure>
 </sect2>

 <sect2 xml:id="sec.s4s.install.sap.product">
  <title>Installing an SAP Product</title>
  <tip>
   <title>Installing an SAP Product in a Fully Installed System</title>
   <para>
    This process is documented as it appears during the installation workflow.
    However, there is a functionally equivalent &yast; dialog available within
    the installed system.
    It has a different color scheme and lacks the left pane.
   </para>
   <para>
    To start it, from the desktop, choose
    <menuchoice><guimenu>Applications</guimenu><guimenu>System</guimenu>
    <guimenu>YaST</guimenu></menuchoice>, continue in the &yast; control center
    by choosing
    <menuchoice><guimenu>Miscellaneous</guimenu>
    <guimenu>SAP Product Installer</guimenu></menuchoice>.
   </para>
  </tip>
  <tip>
   <title>SAP Product Installer Configuration</title>
   <remark>
    The terminological discrepancy between "SAP Product Installer" and
    "SAP Installation Wizard" is pretty annoying. - sknorr, 2016-01-15
   </remark>
   <para>
    The SAP Product Installer configuration are specified and
    documented in
    <filename>/etc/sysconfig/sap-installation-wizard</filename>. You can
    change them according to your needs.
   </para>
  </tip>

  <procedure>
   <step>
    <para>
     In the screen <guimenu>SAP Installation Wizard</guimenu>, provide the <guimenu>Location of the SAP Installation
     Master</guimenu> (<xref linkend="fig.s4s.sap.wizard.source"/>). The
     location can either be a local, removable, or remote installation source.
    </para>
    <figure xml:id="fig.s4s.sap.wizard.source">
     <title>SAP Installation Wizard: SAP Installation Master Location</title>
     <mediaobject>
      <imageobject role="fo">
       <imagedata fileref="s4s_sap_wizard_source.png" width="80%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject role="html">
       <imagedata fileref="yast-start-sap-install.png" width="80%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
     </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    <para>
     Select the corresponding option from the drop-down box.
     In the text box, specify the path to your source according to the format
     given in the following table.
    </para>

    <informaltable>
     <tgroup cols="3">
      <colspec colnum="1" colname="option" colwidth="15*"/>
      <colspec colnum="2" colname="desc" colwidth="30*"/>
      <colspec colnum="3" colname="format" colwidth="55*"/>
      <thead>
       <row>
        <entry>
         <para>
          Option
         </para>
        </entry>
        <entry>
         <para>
          Description
         </para>
        </entry>
        <entry>
         <para>
          Format of Path
         </para>
        </entry>
       </row>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
       <row>
        <entry namest="option" nameend="format">
         <emphasis role="strong">Local Sources</emphasis>
        </entry>
       </row>
       <row>
        <entry>
         <para>
          <guimenu>dir://</guimenu>
         </para>
        </entry>
        <entry>
         <para>
          a local directory
         </para>
        </entry>
        <entry>
         <para>
          <filename><replaceable>/path/to/dir/</replaceable></filename>
         </para>
        </entry>
       </row>
       <row>
        <entry namest="option" nameend="format">
         <emphasis role="strong">Removable Sources</emphasis>
        </entry>
       </row>
       <row>
        <entry>
         <para>
          <guimenu>device://</guimenu>
         </para>
        </entry>
        <entry>
         <para>
          a locally connected hard disk
         </para>
        </entry>
        <entry>
         <para>
          <filename><replaceable>devicename</replaceable><replaceable>/path/to/dir/on/device</replaceable></filename>
         </para>
        </entry>
       </row>
       <row>
        <entry>
         <para>
          <guimenu>usb://</guimenu>
         </para>
        </entry>
        <entry>
         <para>
          a USB mass storage device
         </para>
        </entry>
        <entry>
         <para>
          <filename><replaceable>/path/to/dir/on/USB</replaceable></filename>
         </para>
        </entry>
       </row>
       <row>
        <entry>
         <para>
          <guimenu>cdrom://</guimenu>
         </para>
        </entry>
        <entry>
         <para>
          a CD-ROM
          <remark>What about DVDs? - sknorr, 2016-01-15</remark>
         </para>
        </entry>
        <entry>
         <para>
          <filename><replaceable>//</replaceable></filename>
         </para>
        </entry>
       </row>
       <row>
        <entry namest="option" nameend="format">
         <emphasis role="strong">Remote Sources</emphasis>
        </entry>
       </row>
       <row>
        <entry>
         <para>
          <guimenu>nfs://</guimenu>
         </para>
        </entry>
        <entry>
         <para>
          an NFS share
         </para>
        </entry>
        <entry>
         <para>
          <filename><replaceable>devicename</replaceable><replaceable>/path/to/dir/on/device</replaceable></filename>
         </para>
        </entry>
       </row>
       <row>
        <entry>
         <para>
          <guimenu>smb://</guimenu>
         </para>
        </entry>
        <entry>
         <para>
          an SMB share
         </para>
        </entry>
        <entry>
         <para>
          <filename>[<replaceable>username</replaceable>:<replaceable>password</replaceable>@]<replaceable>server_name</replaceable>/<replaceable>/path/to/dir/on/server</replaceable>[?workgroup=<replaceable>workgroup_name</replaceable>]</filename>
         </para>
        </entry>
       </row>
      </tbody>
     </tgroup>
    </informaltable>

    <tip>
     <title>Remote Location Specification</title>
     <para>
      To install from an NFS source, enter the name of
      the server and the complete path to the media data. For more
      information about setting up a remote installation server, see
      <xref linkend="sec.s4s.install.sap.mediaset"/>.
     </para>
    </tip>

    <remark>
     It seems likely to me that I have not grasped the gravity of this UI elm.
     Needs update. - sknorr, 2016-01-15
    </remark>
    <para>
     If your system is already an installation server (<quote>Software
     Provisioning Master</quote>), you can additionally choose your own system
     as the provider of the installation master.
     To do so, use the drop-down box below <guimenu>Choose an installation
     master</guimenu>.
    </para>
   </step>
   <step>
    <para>
     Under <guimenu>Advanced Options</guimenu>, choose from among the follwing
     options:
    </para>
    <variablelist>
     <varlistentry>
      <term>
       <guimenu>Collect installation profile but do not execute
        installation</guimenu>
      </term>
      <listitem>
       <remark>
        Is any of this true? This was just copied from the description of an
        option existing in SLES for SAP 12 GA. - sknorr, 2016-01-15
       </remark>
       <para>
        Use this option if you only want to set the installation parameters,
        but not perform the actual installation now.
        The installer will copy the product images to
        <filename>/data/SAP_CDs</filename> and prepare an installation
        environment for every product as follows:
       </para>
<screen><![CDATA[/data/SAP_INST/0/Instmaster
/data/SAP_INST/1/Instmaster
/data/SAP_INST/2/Instmaster
...]]></screen>
       <para>
        To run an automatic installation, start by setting
        <literal>SAP_AUTO_INSTALL="yes"</literal> in
        <filename>/etc/sysconfig/sap-installation-wizard</filename>.
       </para>
       <para>
        If you then
        click the <guimenu>SAP Product Installer</guimenu> in the &yast;
        Control Center to run the auto installation, all settings will be
        displayed and offered for optional fine-tuning (NetWeaver) or the
        parameters are written to the &ay; files in the
        <filename>/data/SAP_INST/<replaceable>number</replaceable></filename>
        directories, where you can modify them according to your needs
        (HANA/Business One).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>
     <varlistentry>
      <term>
       <guimenu>Link to the installation master without copying its content to
       local location (SAP NetWeaver only)</guimenu>
      </term>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Use this option to avoid copying an installation master from one
        local location to another.
        This option is only active when the drop-down box above is set to
        <guimenu>dir://</guimenu>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>
     <varlistentry>
      <term>
       <guimenu>Serve all installation media (including master) to local
       network via NFS</guimenu>
      </term>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Set up this system as an installation server (<quote>Software
        Provisioning Master</quote>) for other &sles4sap;
        systems.
        The media copied to this installation server will be offer through
        Service Location Protocol (SLP).
       </para>
       <remark>
        Might be best to add a separate procedure for this. - sknorr, 2016-01-15
       </remark>
       <remark>
        Also, I don't quite get why this option should be available only
        together with an installation/preparation for an installation.
        Need to ask varkoly. - sknorr, 2016-01-15
       </remark>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
    <para>
     Proceed with <guimenu>Next</guimenu>.
    </para>
   </step>
   <step>
    <remark>
     Would this fit? "When the SAP installation master you selected is based on
     NetWeaver..." - sknorr, 2016-01-15
    </remark>
    <para>
     When installing a NetWeaver application, you will now see the screen
     <guimenu>What Would You Like to Install</guimenu>.
     Under <guimenu>The SAP product is</guimenu>, choose the how you want to
     install the product:
    </para>
    <remark>
     Complete this list with help from the Help button? Or remove? (As before?)
    </remark>
    <variablelist>
     <varlistentry>
      <term><guimenu>SAP Standard System</guimenu></term>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Install a standard product.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>
     <varlistentry>
      <term><guimenu>SAP Standalone Engines</guimenu></term>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Engines that add functionality to a standard product.
       </para>
       <remark>
        Why is "engines" in plural? This is certainly not a typo, it was the
        same way before the redesign. - sknorr, 2016-01-15
       </remark>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>
     <varlistentry>
      <term><guimenu>Distributed System</guimenu></term>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        A product that is separated onto multiple servers.
       </para>
       <remark>
        UI inconsistency? Why is this not called "SAP Distributed System"?
        - sknorr, 2016-01-15
       </remark>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>
     <varlistentry>
      <term><guimenu>SAP High-Availability System</guimenu></term>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Installation of
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>
     <varlistentry>
      <term><guimenu>System Rename</guimenu></term>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Rename an existing installation.
       </para>
       <remark>
        Should this be a different procedure? - sknorr, 2016-01-15
       </remark>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
    <para>
     If you selected <guimenu>SAP Standard System</guimenu>,
     <guimenu>Distributed System</guimenu>, or
     <guimenu>SAP High-Availability System</guimenu>,
     additionally choose a back-end database under
     <guimenu>The back-end database system is</guimenu>.
    </para>
    <para>
     Proceed with <guimenu>Next</guimenu>
    </para>
    <figure xml:id="fig.s4s.sap.wizard.mode.db">
     <title>SAP Installation Wizard: Installation Mode and Database</title>
     <mediaobject>
      <imageobject role="fo">
       <imagedata fileref="s4s_sap_wizard_mode_db.png" width="80%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject role="html">
       <imagedata fileref="s4s_sap_wizard_mode_db.png" width="80%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
     </mediaobject>
    </figure>
   </step>
   <step>
    <para>
     In case of a NetWeaver installation you now select a <guimenu>SAP
     Product</guimenu>. The offerings of available products depend on the
     media set and installation master you received from SAP; for example,
     see <xref linkend="fig.s4s.sap.wizard.avail.products"/>.
    </para>
    <figure xml:id="fig.s4s.sap.wizard.avail.products">
     <title>SAP Installation Wizard: SAP Products</title>
     <mediaobject>
      <imageobject role="fo">
       <imagedata fileref="s4s_sap_wizard_available_products.png" width="80%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject role="html">
       <imagedata fileref="s4s_sap_wizard_available_products.png" width="80%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
     </mediaobject>
    </figure>
   </step>

   <step xml:id="pro.install.sap.wizard.products">
    <para>
     For example, select <guimenu>SAP NetWeaver 7.4</guimenu> and click
     <guimenu>Next</guimenu>. Now the relevant part of the SAP media will be
     copied to the hard drive of the machine for the following SAP
     installation (after copying, see the contents of
     <filename>/data/SAP_CDs</filename>; the layout is explained later in
     this chapter). This is repeated for all necessary SAP media, with some
     additional simple questions.
    </para>
   </step>
   <step>
    <para>
     You are asked to provide the <guimenu>Location of the SAP
     Medium</guimenu> and if additional media are needed, you can also add
     them afterwards; see <xref linkend="fig.s4s.sap.wizard.sapmedia"/>
     (here you see the list of already copied or linked SAP media). Click
     <guimenu>Help</guimenu> for information.
     <!--
        In this case, it would be NWKERNEL; see <xref
        linkend="fig.s4s.sap.wizard.nwkernel"/>.
     -->
    </para>
    <!--
       <figure id="fig.s4s.sap.wizard.nwkernel">
      <title>SAP Installation Wizard: Location of the SAP Medium</title>
      <mediaobject>
       <imageobject role="fo">
        <imagedata fileref="s4s_sap_wizard_location_nwkernel.png" width="80%" format="PNG"/>
       </imageobject>
       <imageobject role="html">
        <imagedata fileref="s4s_sap_wizard_location_nwkernel.png" width="80%" format="PNG"/>
       </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
      </figure>
    -->
    <figure xml:id="fig.s4s.sap.wizard.sapmedia">
     <title>SAP Installation Wizard: Additional SAP Media</title>
     <mediaobject>
      <imageobject role="fo">
       <imagedata fileref="s4s_sap_wizard_location_sapmedia.png" width="80%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject role="html">
       <imagedata fileref="s4s_sap_wizard_location_sapmedia.png" width="80%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
     </mediaobject>
    </figure>
   </step>
