      </imageobject>
      <imageobject role="html">
       <imagedata fileref="s4s_sap_wizard_step4_installation_type.png" width="80%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
     </mediaobject>
    </figure>
   </step>
   <step>
    <para>
     As step 5 enter the location of the
     <guimenu>Export Media</guimenu> (e.g., the SAP CRM Installation
     Export DVD); see <xref
     linkend="fig.s4s.sap.wizard.location.export.medium"/> for an NFS
     installation example.
    </para>

     <figure id="fig.s4s.sap.wizard.location.export.medium">
     <title>SAP Installation: Location of the Export Media</title>
     <mediaobject>
      <imageobject role="fo">
       <imagedata fileref="s4s_sap_wizard_step5_export_media.png" width="80%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
      <imageobject role="html">
       <imagedata fileref="s4s_sap_wizard_step5_export_media.png" width="80%" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
     </mediaobject>
    </figure>

    <para>
     If needed, add the additional export media when installation wizard
     asks about it.
    </para>
    </step>
   -->
   <step>
    <para>
     Then you can optionally copy a <guimenu>Supplement</guimenu> or
     <guimenu>Third-Party Medium</guimenu>. For more information about a
     Supplement Media, see <xref linkend="sec.s4s.component.supplement"/>.
    </para>
   </step>
   <step>
    <para>
     At this point, all data (product images) required for the SAP
     installation is selected and copied to
     <filename>/data/SAP_CDs</filename>, one directory per medium, e.g.:
    </para>
